body:
@laanwj Thanks for the heads up. I rebased on top of 5.12 and tested on an Android 11 device.

@prayank23 I can't comment on other approaches. This PR aims to bring nothing less (and nothing more) than `bitcoin-qt` running on Android. https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16883 is an attempt to make the GUI a bit more modern and usable but it's parked for now as I can't find the time to work on it.

BTW everyone check out the testnet IBD:
![Screenshot_20210321-161502](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/762502/111911965-e5681400-8a67-11eb-9128-1dd5315a01fb.jpg)
That seems quite fast, no? And the phone's not even warm.... This PR might make practical sense after all. :sunglasses:

@ryanofsky Yes, and this line is the culprit:
https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/9217f9fe7351d9c36803456f88ae561e23f17ac9/src/Makefile.qt.include#L382

Is Cirrus perhaps wiping `depends/sources` from time to time?

